00:33:11.278 --> 00:33:14.858
Essentially what you have is a lox stop lox.

578
00:33:15.108 --> 00:33:18.718
So this is a Cre-inducible Cas9 that also expresses

579
00:33:18.818 --> 00:33:19.318
GFP.

580
00:33:20.198 --> 00:33:22.658
This is in all of the cells in its germline.

581
00:33:23.118 --> 00:33:26.858
So you can isolate urothelial cells and then grow them

582
00:33:27.778 --> 00:33:30.718
ex vivo in 3D Matrigel as organoids.

583
00:33:32.298 --> 00:33:36.147
And then we treat them with a Cre induction,

584
00:33:37.178 --> 00:33:40.998
and then we can actually induce point mutations with guide

585
00:33:41.078 --> 00:33:44.918
RNAs in p53, and then we also can induce

586
00:33:45.758 --> 00:33:49.098
loss of the chromosomal segment, a 9p21

587
00:33:49.698 --> 00:33:51.778
homologous segment in mice.

588
00:33:51.818 --> 00:33:55.578
The same

589
00:33:55.638 --> 00:33:56.778
three genes are the same

590
00:33:58.198 --> 00:34:00.038
in mice and in humans.

591
00:34:01.338 --> 00:34:04.338
And then as an additional hit,

592
00:34:05.238 --> 00:34:05.498
we

593
00:34:07.618 --> 00:34:10.298
generated a hotspot point mutation that we actually just heard the last speaker

